-- Freezes the OpenStreetMap import as permanent, versioned data.
--
-- The OSM/Overpass importer (OverpassRestaurantProvider, ImportController) fetches
-- live from the Overpass API via an admin-triggered action — it is NOT idempotent
-- via a fresh database volume, so a brand-new environment previously started with
-- only the 14 fictional dev-seed restaurants until someone manually re-ran the
-- import. This migration bakes the 295 real Tokyo restaurants fetched on
-- 2026-07-24 in as permanent, versioned data — a fresh `docker compose up` now has
-- real data from the first boot, with no manual step and no live network call.
--
-- This is a point-in-time snapshot, not a live sync: it will not pick up new venues
-- OSM contributors add later, or edits to existing ones. Re-running the admin import
-- endpoint (POST /api/v1/admin/imports/openstreetmap) still works to refresh this —
-- both this migration's rows and a live re-import upsert on the same
-- (source, source_external_id) key, so they cannot create duplicates or conflict.
--
-- Generated from a live import; not hand-written. To regenerate after a future
-- re-import, dump `restaurants`/`restaurant_categories` WHERE source =
-- 'OPENSTREETMAP' and rebuild this file's VALUES lists the same way.

